<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1334">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/534.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 28. Assembly refuses to authorize sale of entire railroad.
                            Only two possible courses now open: (1) bankers to exercise <pb facs="1143" n="1039" xml:id="pg_1039"/> option on 51% and reimburse
                            themselves for existing indebtedness, thereby releasing all Government
                            revenues; or (2) bankers to release all securities except railroad, the
                            option on 51% of which to continue until discharge of the debt.
                            President Diaz feels that the bankers are unreasonable in insisting on
                            the same security now, when the debt is only $400,000, as when it was
                            $2,500,000. The situation is critical.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Weitzel</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>